1 Install Openssh in ubuntu using apt
 - sudo apt install openssh-server
2 update the apt List
 - sudo apt update
3 install VLC player
 - sudo apt-get install vlc
4 change your DNS to 8.8.8.8 and 8.8.4.4
 - sudo vi /etc/resolv.conf
5 Secure the SSH ( put all what you know in the configuration file)

6 How can you find out how much memory Linux is using?
 - cat /proc/meminfo
7 What is a typical size for a swap partition under a Linux system?
 - Twice the size of RAM if RAM is less than 2 GB
 - Size of RAM + 2 GB if RAM size is more than 2 GB i.e. 5GB of swap for 3GB of RAM
8 what is the version of BASH in your system?
 - version 4.4.19(1)-release
9 write Hello world program in Bash
 - mkdir scripts
 - cd scripts
 - nano helloworld.sh
 - #!/bin/bash
   echo "hello world"
10 Run the Program 
 - to open script: sh helloworld.sh
 - sudo chmod +x helloworld.sh
 - ./helloworld.sh
